The proposed ensemble learning method assigns a weight to each network based on its performance. If a classifier performs better, it is assigned a higher weight. First, the weights are scaled to values between 0 and 1. Then, for each weight vector, the combination of weights that has the highest accuracy in predicting the disease stages is selected. These optimized weights are applied in the final stage of the ensemble learning method. The weighted ensemble learning formula is given in Eq. (7):7\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
